1. *Blagoslovio* je svog sina pre nego što je krenuo na put. (He *blessed* his son before he went on a journey.)
2. Ova crkva je *blagoslovio* patrijarh. (This church was *blessed* by the patriarch.)
3. *Blagoslovio* sam hranu pre nego što smo počeli da jedemo. (I *blessed* the food before we started eating.)
4. Ona je molila Boga da je *blagoslovi* pre važnog sastanka. (She prayed to God to *bless* her before an important meeting.)
5. Sveštenik je *blagoslovio* novu kuću. (The priest *blessed* the new house.)
6. Roditelji su *blagoslovili* brak svoje ćerke. (The parents *blessed* their daughter's marriage.)
7. Poglavar crkve je *blagoslovio* vernike. (The head of the church *blessed* the believers.)
8. *Blagoslovio* je sve one koji su učestvovali u humanitarnoj akciji. (He *blessed* everyone who participated in the humanitarian action.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "blagoslovio" comes from the verb "blagosloviti", which means "to bless". The word can be used in different forms depending on the tense and the subject of the sentence.